		"S" => array(
			5 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber and the maximum flame-spread rating as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			6 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams or columns constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			7 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams and columns is equal or less than 150.",
			8 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber and the maximum flame-spread rating as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			9 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			10 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber walls is equal or less than 150.",
			11 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber, flame-spread ratings, and the necessary mass timber wall spacing as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			12 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\n Please adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			13 => "The design of the suite does not comply with required wall spacing for mass timber walls that face each other, as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nAccording to the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada, a mass timber wall must be separated from opposing or adjacent exposed surfaces of a different mass timber wall by a horizontal distance of at least 4.5 meters.",
			14 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls is less than 150.",
			15 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber, flame-spread rating, and the necessary mass timber wall spacing as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			17 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			19 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for any exposed mass timber element is equal or less than 150.",
			20 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute no more than 10% of the total ceiling area of the suite. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for any exposed mass timber element is equal or less than 150.",
			22 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber, flame-spread ratings, and the necessary mass timber wall spacing as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			24 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			26 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute more than 10%, but no more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the suite. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for the exposed mass timber ceiling or wall is equal or less than 75.",
			27 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute more than 10%, but no more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the suite. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams and columns equal or less than 150.",
			28 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute more than 10%, but no more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the suite, including openings. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams and columns is equal or less than 150.",
			29 => "The design of the suite complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber, flame-spread ratings, and the necessary mass timber wall spacing as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			30 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.\nIf mass timber walls are exposed, the exposed wall surfaces must face same direction, or the exposed wall surfaces are separated by a horizontal distance of not less than 4.5 m and all mass timber walls that are not otherwise permitted to be exposed within the allowable 35% (remaining 65%), are protected by a material or assembly of materials that provides an encapsulation rating of not less than 80 min.\nIf there is any remaining percentage from the allowable 35% for exposed walls that is protected by user choice, it can be protected with any level of encapsulation rating, 25, 50, or 80 mins.",
			31 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams, columns and walls constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			32 => "When exposing more than 25% of the mass timber ceiling within a suite, if mass timber walls are exposed, the exposed wall surfaces must face same direction, or the exposed wall surfaces are separated by a horizontal distance of not less than 4.5 m. Also, if any surface of the mass timber walls are exposed within the suite, the mass timber walls that are not otherwise permitted to be exposed within the allowable 35% (remaining 65%), are protected by a material or assembly of materials that provides an encapsulation rating of not less than 80 min.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure 65% of the exposed walls are protected by a material or assembly of materials that provides an encapsulation rating of not less than 80 min. If there is any remaining percentage from the allowable 35% for exposed walls that is protected by user choice, it can be protected with any level of encapsulation rating, 25, 50, or 80 mins.",
			35 => "The current design of the suite does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nAccording to the NBC, when more than 25% of the ceiling is exposed, exposed mass timber beams or columns are permitted up to 20% of the allowable 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings. While walls are not individually limited, they must collectively work with beams and columns to ensure that the total exposed mass timber does not exceed 35% of the total area of the suite perimeter walls, including openings.",
			37 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceiling constitute more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the suite. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for the exposed mass timber ceiling or walls is equal or less than 75.",
			39 => "The design of the suite does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceiling constitute more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the suite. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for the exposed mass timber beams or columns is equal or less than 150.",
		),
		"FC" => array(
			5 => "The design of the fire compartment complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber and the maximum flame-spread rating as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			7 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams or columns constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the fire compartment perimeter walls, including openings.",
			8 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams and columns is up to or less than 150.",
			9 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nExposed mass timber walls are not permitted within fire compartments, only suites as defined by the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			10 => "The design of the fire compartment complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber and flame-spread ratings as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			12 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams and columns constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the fire compartment perimeter walls, including openings.",
			13 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams, columns and ceiling is equal or less than 150.",
			14 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute no more than 10% of the total ceiling area of the fire compartment. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for any exposed mass timber element is equal or less than 150.",
			15 => "The design of the fire compartment complies with the permissible percentage of exposed mass timber and flame-spread ratings as specified in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.",
			17 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the combined exposed mass timber beams and columns constitute no more than 35% of the total area of the fire compartment perimeter walls, including openings.",
			19 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute more than 10%, but no more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the fire compartment. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for the exposed mass timber ceiling is equal or less than 75.",
			21 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable maximum flame-spread rating with the current percentage of exposed mass timber ceiling and as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nPlease adjust the design to ensure that the exposed mass timber ceilings constitute more than 10%, but no more than 25% of the total ceiling area of the fire compartment. Additionally, ensure that the chosen flame-spread rating for exposed mass timber beams and columns is up to or less than 150.",
			22 => "The design of the fire compartment does not comply with the allowable percentage of exposed mass timber as outlined in the 2025 edition of the National Building Code of Canada.\nExposed mass timber ceilings are only permitted up to 25% of the total ceiling area of the fire compartment.",
